<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--ChihuahuaDeath     08-12 0157</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Chihuahua Death,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Sentenced In Chihuahua Death.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two men were sentenced to four to 12 months in
jail for stomping a neighbor's pet Chihuahua to death.
   Anthony Goff, 22, and Shawn Kerr, 19, both of nearby Imperial,
were also ordered Thursday to spend five years on probation and 100
hours doing community service work for the Animal Rescue League of
Western Pennsylvania. The group takes in stray dogs and cats and
tried to find homes for them.
   Both men said they were sorry and embarrassed they stole Co-Co,
a dog belonging to Olive Marie Maximonvich of Imperial.
   Goff and Kerr said they were drunk when they jumped into the
Maximonvich family's fenced yard, tossed the animal into the
street, took it to a nearby garage and stomped it to death. The
dog's corpse later was burned over an open fire.
   Both men pleaded guilty to theft, cruelty to animals and
criminal conspiracy.
</TEXT>
