<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--FinickySheep     08-12 0112</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Finicky Sheep,0113</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Australian Imported Sheep `Aloof,' Dislike Malaysia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sheep imported from Australia
don't like Malaysia and refuse to crossbreed with the local
species, an agricultural official said today.
   Osman Ismail, chairman of the Jempol District Area Farmers
Organization, said his statements were based on the group's
observation of 110 imported ewes, mostly from Australia, that were
reared throughout last year.
   Although the ewes were fed well and fertile, they were ``aloof''
and only one lamb was born to the flock, Ismail said.
   Ismail spoke at the group's annual general meeting at Serting
Hilir, 72 miles south of Kuala Lumpur, the national news agency
Bernama reported.
</TEXT>
