<TEXT>
   Comedian-candidate Pat Paulsen kicked off his
1988 presidential campaign _ his sixth _ by dropping a political
bombshell: he's becoming a Republican.
   ``I'm going to New Orleans _ I have to, because the Democrats
tossed me right out of Atlanta,'' Paulsen said Thursday after
declaring his candidacy. ``They're not very friendly people.''
   Paulsen, who made his first run for the White House 20 years
ago, announced his election bid on a boat in New York Harbor with
the Statue of Liberty in the background.
   The former regular on the ``Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour''
