<HEAD>Building Site Attacked With Chainsaw</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SIMI VALLEY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A carpenter apparently angry over
being denied payment for a construction job used a chainsaw to hack
away at a partially completed building, police said.
   Officers said Ronald W. Fry, 36, caused an estimated $15,000 in
damage to the future site of an extension of a shopping center
Wednesday. He was arrested for investigation of malicious mischief.
   The construction superintendent called police when Fry became
upset after construction officials turned down his request to be
paid in full for $1,200 worth of carpentry work that was
three-quarters completed, police said.
   Fry allegedly cut down poles and damaged one of the building's
walls and some of the electrical conduits, said Michael Hekmat, an
owner of the project.
   Fry was being held at Ventura County jail on $6,000 bail. He
also faces several outstanding warrants, including a probation
violation, jail authorities said.
