<FILEID>AP-NR-08-12-88 0613EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a PM-ChildProstitution     08-12 0382</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Child Prostitution,0392</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Leader Of Boy Sex Ring Once A Teen Prostitute Himself, Police Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who was once a teen-age prostitute has
been charged with running an eight-year-old sex ring that sold the
services of hundreds of boys, sometimes flying them to other
cities, police said.
   Accused ringleader Wesley David Gonzalez, 26, earned a living
from prostitution from age 12 to 16, eventually giving it up to
start the pedophile ring eight years ago, said Detective Robert
Sheehan.
   The Tampa-based operation came to light when the parents of an
11-year-old contacted police after wondering how their son got
large amounts of cash.
   A four-month probe led to the arrests of Gonzalez and two other
Floridians in June, police disclosed Wednesday. The investigation
continues, and authorities say they expect more arrests in other
cities.
   For eight years, the network sent boys to Atlanta, Denver,
Boston, Indianapolis and Chicago to meet adult clients, said Tampa
Sgt. Ronald J. Reynolds.
   Gonzalez, an unemployed avionics technician, understood the
psyche of the boys he hired _ most of them from poor families and
broken homes _ because he was once one of them, Sheehan said. He
used boys to recruit others, flashing wads of cash as a lure,
Sheehan said.
   ``A lot of the kids despised the sex, but the financial
inducements were too enticing to the youngsters,'' said Sheehan.
   The underground child prostitution operation involved hundreds
of youths ages 11 to 16, who earned from $300 to $700 for a single
meeting, police said.
   Getting the boys to admit their activities was difficult because
of a quiet bond between them, and officials said that slowed the
investigation.
   ``The members' loyalty stood even when faced with prison,''
Sheehan said.
   Gonzalez, also known as Michael David Gonzalez, was arrested in
June on a Tampa warrant charging him with capital sexual battery,
procuring children under 16 for prostitution and deriving financial
support from prostitution, according to Sheehan. He is being held
without bond.
   The others arrested were identified as car salesman Larry
Gorman, 38, and Michael Leroy Johnson, 30, who works for a paint
company. Johnson was charged with lewd and lascivious acts with a
child; Gorman was charged with performing a sexual act with a
child. Both were released on bond.
</TEXT>
