<HEAD>Vice-President of State News Agency Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Adrian Ionescu, the vice president of
the Romanian state news agency Agerpres, has died of an unspecified
illness, Hungary's Communist Party daily said today.
   The Bucharest correspondent of the Nepszabadsag daily said the
death was announced briefly in Thursday's edition of the Romanian
government newspaper Romania Libera.
   Ionescu was chairman of the Romanian Journalists' Council and
editor in chief of the weekly Lumea, published for foreigners
interested in Romania.
