<HEAD>67 People Arrested, Weapons Seized</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities stormed a house occupied by
squatters Friday, arresting 67 people and seizing a bazooka and
other weapons, police said. They said two officers were wounded.
   The arrests occurred after six policemen were injured Thursday
in a raid on a neighboring house occupied by squatters. The
squatters fled into an adjacent property, and police obtained a
court order to search that house Friday.
   An earthmover was used to smash one wall after the squatters
refused to leave. Police then entered the building and made the
arrests. Reporters saw police dragging at least one person who was
unconscious from the house.
   Police said they seized a bazooka, two pistols, bullets, knives
and chains. The house seized by police Thursday was largely
demolished during the night. Both properties are to be torn down
for a small park.
