<1ST_LINE>r i BC-Burma-ResignationText     08-12 0359</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Burma-Resignation Text,0363</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Text Of Radio Rangoon's Announcement Of President's Resignation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the full text of the
announcement Friday on Burma's official Radio Rangoon on the
resignation of Burmese President Sein Lwin. The Burmese-language
broadcast was monitored in Bangkok and translated by The Associated
Press. ``U'' is an honorific in the Burmese language.
   It is learned that since the chairman of the Burma Socialist
Program Party presented that he be allowed to resign from the post
of chairman of the Burma Socialist Program Party and from the
Central Committee of the party, the 92nd meeting of the Central
Executive Committee held on Aug. 12, 1988, has accepted his
resignation.
   As regards the Council of State of the Socialist Republic of the
Union of Burma allowing U Sein Lwin to resign from the post of
chairman of the Council of State, from the duties as president of
the state, and from the People's Assembly as a member, the
notification No. 108-88, dated today, Aug. 12, 1988, has been
issued.
   The specifics of the notification: ``As U Sein Lwin presented
that he be allowed to resign from the post of chairman of the
Council of State, from his duties as president of the state, and
from the People's Assembly as a member from ... Moulmein, Mon
State, U Sein Lwin is allowed to resign with effect from today,
Aug. 12, 1988, from the post of chairman of the Council of State,
from his duties as president of the state and as a member of the
People's Assembly from ... Moulmein, Mon State. Signed Kyaw Htin,
Secretary, Council of State.''
   Notification No. 6-88 of today, Aug. 12, 1988: ``In accordance
with section 51 of the Constitution, it is announced that the
Council of State calls for the fourth emergency session of the
People's Assembly to be held on Friday, Aug. 19, 1988, 10 a.m. in
Rangoon. Signed Aye Ko, Vice Chairman, Council of State.''
   The Central Committee of the Burma Socialist Program Party will
be meeting on Aug. 19, 1988 at 8:30 a.m. All members of the Central
Committee have to report by Aug. 18, 1988.
</TEXT>
