<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>Fire Spreads From 86th to 102nd Floor</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire broke out today on the 86th floor of the
Empire State Building, and moved up a shaftway to the 102nd floor
at the top of the skyscraper, the Fire Department said.
   No injuries were reported immediately and no people were
trapped, but firefighters were having trouble with water pressure
in fighting the higher blaze, said Efrain Parrilla, a department
spokesman.
   Several floors were evacuated because of smoke while the 86th
floor fire, a small blaze in a utility room, was extinguished,
Parrilla said. The 86th floor houses the main observatory.
   The alarm had sounded automatically at 1:02 p.m., he said, and
the fire was quickly put out.
   The 102nd-floor fire was discovered at 1:48 p.m.
