<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Brites     08-12 0382</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Brites,0395</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bright and Brief</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RENO, Nev. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   If it's Tuesday, this must be the day to water
your lawn _but only if you live in a home with an odd-numbered
address or you own a business. Got it straight?
   Don't feel too bad if you don't, for Reno's new water
conservation ordinance even tripped up Mayor Pete Sferrazza, and he
voted for the thing.
   Sferrazza, who lives at an even-numbered address, sprinkled his
lawn on Tuesday and Thursday this week instead of on Wednesday and
Saturday as required under the ordinance. His neighbors were only
too happy to report him.
   The mayor said a Reno nursery had installed a sprinkler system
in his yard and he assumed it was adjusted to water on the allowed
days.
   ``I've got to change my timer,'' Sferrazza said Thursday. ``I
can change it today. In any event, I'll take care of it.''
   Westpac Utilities spokeswoman Bonnie Saviers said the mayor
isn't the only one confused by the irrigation schedule. Questions
to her office have doubled since the ordinance went into effect
Monday, she said.
   Under the rules, even numbered addresses may water on Wednesdays
and Saturdays, odd numbered addresses on Thursdays and Sundays,
businesses on Tuesdays and Fridays and no one on Mondays.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Speedy swine with names like Fried Bacon,
Alberto Clipper, New Deal Charlie and Joan Jett hoofed it toward
the finish line at the Ohio State Fair, but when it was all over
the porker in the winner's circle was Turbo Pig.
   ``He's just a really fast pig,'' said Amy Herbkersman of
Collins, who took home $234 for T.P.'s winning race Thursday. ``I
give him really good feed, but I don't train him much. He's just
feisty and fast.''
   Not as fast as last year's winner, though: Turbo Pig's winning
time was 3.9 seconds, well off the 2.7-second record set in 1987 by
Squealing Demon.
   The fair's 10th annual pig race drew 15 contestants.
   Ms. Herbkersman said her family racing team got into racing by
mistake.
   ``I found out about an offer to get a free pig,'' she said. ``I
didn't realize that one condition of accepting the pig was to race
it. But now my family and I caught the bug and we love it.''
</TEXT>
