<1ST_LINE>r a AM-TripToDentist     08-12 0374</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Trip To Dentist,0382</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Who Took 1,100-Mile Detour Finally Gets Dentures</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PELL CITY, Ala. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who set out for his dental clinic
and took an unintended 1,120-mile detour last month finally reached
the dentist's chair, where he was rewarded with free dentures.
   ``I ain't embarrassed,'' said 76-year-old Frank Collier of
Centreville. ``It could've happened to anybody.''
   In fact, it almost happened to Collier's friend, 80-year-old
Deacon Brisco Huff, who agreed to drive Collier from Centreville to
the dental clinic 74 miles away in Pell City on Thursday.
   Huff took two wrong turns and had to stop six times to ask for
directions.
   ``I got lost, too, but I was determined not to go as far as he
went,'' said Huff.
   Collier, a retired mill worker who had never left west Alabama
except for one other trip to Pell City, ended up driving 560 miles
_ all the way to Muncie, Ind., before he found out how far off
course he had gone. Police in Muncie helped Collier get in touch
with family and friends, who drove him back.
   ``They told me they didn't think I'd better drive no more,''
Collier said Thursday. ``I told them that was fine with me because
I was tired of it.''
   ``I was trying to follow the road this fellow took when he
brought me up here the first time I came, a long time ago,''
Collier explained. ``I thought I could find my way back my own
self. I got on that interstate (I-65) and didn't know how to get
off. I just kept a-goin', kept a-goin', right out of the state,
almost out of the country.''
   Joining Collier and Huff on the trip Thursday was Huff's wife,
Iola, who was stationed in the front seat with a map of Alabama on
her lap.
   When Collier finally arrived at Dr. Joe Sawyer's clinic _ 30
minutes late _ the dentist gave his most famous patient a free set
of dentures, with two gold teeth in front.
   As Collier and the Huffs departed, Mrs. Huff said they probably
would be back in Centreville by late afternoon. But then, thinking
of other possibilities, she added, ``We just may end up in Florida.
You never know.''
</TEXT>
