<HEAD>Mark and Brigitte Announce Engagement, Sealed With Tattoos</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PAT MILTON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>UNIONDALE, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Football star Mark Gastineau and actress
Brigitte Nielsen announced Friday that they plan a winter wedding,
as soon as his divorce is final.
   It will be a small, private ceremony attended by ``true
friends,'' Nielsen said at a crowded news conference.
   ``We want something very romantic,'' said Nielsen, 25, who
recently was divorced from actor Sylvester Stallone and has a
4{-year-old son, Julian, who lives with his father, her first
husband, in her native Denmark.
   No date has been set for the nuptials because Gastineau, a New
York Jets defensive end, has yet to sever his marriage to his first
wife, Lisa, a model. They split in 1986 and have a daughter,
Britanny, 5.
   Gastineau and Nielsen were rumored to have had an on-again
off-again engagement after they met during the Super Bowl in
January, but this time it's ``true love,'' they beamed, kissing in
front of hordes of television lights and photographers.
   The couple acknowledged last month's reports that as a symbol of
their eternal love, they have had their names tatooed on each
others buttocks.
   ``It means I really love this person and I'm going to be with
her for eternity,'' said Gastineau, 31, who is attending Jets
training camp at Hofstra University in Hempstead.
   ``I can really call this true love,'' said the bride-to-be, who
proudly showed off her ring, diamonds in the shape of a nine,
reminiscent of Gastineau's jersey number, 99. ``I am the happiest I
have ever been.''
   ``We want lots of kids, 10 of them,'' declared Nielsen, who said
her movie career will be secondary to ``being with Mark.''
   She had a miscarriage last May while filming in Rome.
   ``The miscarriage is one of the most misfortunate things that
ever happened to both of us,'' said Gastineau. ``It tore us apart.''
