<HEAD>10 Women Die When Boat Capsizes In Ganges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A boat capsized in the flooded Ganges
River and at least 10 women died, it was reported Friday. The
incident happened near where more than 400 people drowned in a
ferry accident last week.
   The latest accident occurred Thursday in the Begusarai district
in the northeastern state of Bihar, United News of India said.
   The victims were grass-cutters crossing the Ganges to reach
clusters of wild grass, it said.
   It did not say how many people were on the boat or why it
capsized.
   More than 400 people drowned Aug. 6 when a ferry crossing the
river at Katihar, also in Bihar state, capsized after hitting a
sand bar.
   The Ganges has been flooded since the annual monsoon gripped the
region in June.
