<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Auction,0108</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cash Management Bills Yield 7.73 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Treasury Department has auctioned 248-day
cash management bills at an average discount rate of 7.73 percent.
   The discount rate in Thursday's auction understates the actual
return to investors _ 8.19 percent with a $10,000 bill selling for
$9,467.50.
   A total of $7.0 billion in bills with a minimum denomination of
$10,000 were sold out of bids totaling $25.7 billion.
   The bills will be repaid on April 20, 1989 and are being sold to
help smooth government revenue flows, which normally surge in April
as people pay their income taxes.
</TEXT>
