<2ND_LINE>PM-Misspelled Coin,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Sales Of Misspelled Coin Are Beautitul, Uh, Beautiful</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROANOKE, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sales of Roanoke County's sesquicentennial
coin are proving that good spelling isn't always good business _
collectors and the curious are seeking to obtain coins that
misspell the word ``beautiful'' as ``beautitul.''
   ``As far as we can tell, we're getting more calls since the
mistake was found,'' said Carolyn Wagner of the sesquicentennial
committee. ``I think people mainly are calling to get the coins
with the misspelling, but if they can't get those, they want the
correct ones.''
   Even some banks have called asking for the misspelled coins,
which are being sold in commemoration of the county's founding in
1838, Ms. Wagner said.
   A county employee discovered the blunder after 300 coins had
been sold.
   The misspelled ``beautiful'' was correct in a proof county
officials saw. A minter has acknowledged making the error.
</TEXT>
